==English==

===Etymology===
Greek (''hēdonē''), meaning ''pleasure.'' (Eng. usg. 1856)

===Noun===
'''hedonism'''

# {{Theology}} The belief that [[pleasure]] or happiness is the highest good in life. Some hedonists, such as the Epicureans, have insisted that pleasure of the entire mind, not just pleasure of the senses, is the highest good.
# A lifestyle based on or implying [[w:Hedonists|hedonism]].

